
CURRENT_DOCKER_FILE
===============================
FROM python:3.5-buster
ADD . .
ENV FLASK_APP=app.py
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
CMD flask run --port 7777

UPDATED_DOCKER_FILE
--------------------------------------------------
Hello Fido,

Please follow the below steps for each step with explanation

#start from base
1.FROM python:3.5-buster

2.LABEL maintainer="Your Name <emailaddress@provider.com>"
Please add the details of label for best practices

3.RUN apt-get update -y && apt-get install -y python-pip python-dev
apt-get update downloads the package lists from the repositories and "updates" them to get information on the 
newest versions of packages and their dependencies. It will do this for all repositories and PPAs

4.COPY ./requirements.txt /app/requirements.txt
We need to copy the requirements.txt first to leverage Docker cache

5.WORKDIR /app
Create a folder for workdir isolated to it

6.RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

7.COPY . /app
copy the app folder to current dir

8.CMD [ "python", "./app.py" ]
Execute using the python script file python ./app.py

================================================================
Post that
-----------
setup code and configuration of a Flask application on docker. 
Now execute the below-mentioned docker command to install and run the sample application.

$docker build -t flask:latest

$docker run -p 7777:7777 flask

$docker ps -a
